Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta (LSF) nanoparticles were infiltrated into porous YSZ scaffold to fabricate composite LSF-YSZ oxygen electrode for both solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) and solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC).
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) pattern and scanning electron microscopy (SEM) images have demonstrated that the formation of LSF perovskite phase and uniform distribution of nano-structural LSF particles onto inner surface of the YSZ scaffold, respectively.
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Polarization curves and electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS) were employed for the characterization of electrochemical properties of the cell for both power generation and high-temperature steam electrolysis.
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, the long-term durability of the LSF-infiltrated cell was galvanostatically carried out under both SOFC and SOEC operations.
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: For SOFC operation, the cell experienced a significant degradation in the initial 50 h and subsequently was sustained at a stable operation, with overall ohmic and polarization resistance variation from 0.20 to 0.25 Omega cm(2) and from 0.55 to 0.60 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: For SOEC operation, the cell showed high long-term durability operation, with almost unchangeable ohmic resistance and slightly varied polarization resistance from 0.41 to 0.43 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ nanoparticles into YSZ scaffold for solid oxide fuel cell and solid oxide electrolysis cell
